<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 93 / Arts: Arts award
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONY THORNCROFT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SHORT list was announced yesterday for the 1993 Prudential Awards for
the Arts which is worth Pounds 100,000 writes Antony Thorncroft.
The five on the short list all of whom receive Pounds 25,000, are Shobana
Jeyasingh, who merges dance styles; The Series (a fusion by Birmingham
Contemporary Music Group and Birmingham Jazz); Opera North; Theatre de
Complicite; and Portfolio Gallery.
The Pounds 10,000 Arts Council award for an individual to commission a new
work will go to either Sir Peter Wright, of the Birmingham Royal Ballet;
Nancy Meckler, of Shared Experience; Oliver Knussen, of the Aldeburgh
Festival; Sir Edward Downes, of the Royal Opera House; or Jenni Lomax, of
Camden Arts Centre.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P792  Producers, Orchestras, Entertainers.
</IN>
<XX>
Types:-
</XX>
<TP>NEWS  General News.
</TP>
<PUB>The Financial Times
