<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 93 / Study highlights invalidity benefit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A government-commissioned survey today shows that family doctors consider
patients' job prospects as well as medical conditions when issuing
statements for invalidity benefit.
The report by the Social and Community Planning Research unit, showed that
some doctors continued to sign forms declaring them too ill to work if they
felt there was no real prospect of a patient finding a job.
