<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 93 / BR will cut some fares by 25%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SOME off-peak InterCity rail fares are to be cut by 25 per cent from the
beginning of next month.
In an effort to attract more northbound passengers from the south of
England, InterCity is making the cuts on Apex tickets between 190 south-east
stations and West Yorkshire from October 3. In addition, the number of seats
available to Apex ticketholders travelling from King's Cross to West
Yorkshire will be increased by 750 to 3,000 a week.
