<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 93 / British Association for the Advancement of Science: Fillings
for teeth come unstuck
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THERE ARE a range of new dentistry materials for filling teeth, but although
most of them look better they do not stick well enough to replace
old-fashioned amalgam.
Dr Tim Watson, of Guy's Hospital, London, is carrying out microscopic
investigations of the interface between the filling and the tooth, to trace
the distribution of adhesive components within the tooth. 'This will enable
us to design better materials, and improve cavity preparation to make
fillings last longer,' he said.
