<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 93 / Labour still ahead in Norway
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Norway's ruling minority Labour party has slipped slightly in the polls 10
days before the general election, but still has a clear lead over the main
opposition Conservative party.
According to a poll in Aftenposten, Norway's leading daily, support for
Labour has fallen by 1.7 percentage points to 33.4 per cent, while backing
for the pro-EC Conservative party slipped 1.6 points to 20 per cent.
Support for the small anti-EC Centre party fell 0.9 points to 10.6 per cent.
The Socialist Left party, also opposed to EC membership, rose 2.7 points to
12.8 per cent.
