<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Some Australian wool sale reports are a little brighter this week, but
improved buying interest is confined mainly to Western Europe and China,
with Japan, normally in the lead, only providing support. Prices are
generally unchanged with occasional instances of slight easing, and some
higher prices paid for carding wools which a few days ago were appreciably
cheaper to buy. Traders in wool remain highly cautious in considering the
chance of price rises, as long as the Australian stockpile overhangs the
market. The AWC market indicator on September 1 stood at 411c/kg, the same
as a week earlier.
