<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 93 / International Company News: Burns Philp increases payout
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BURNS Philp, the Australian food technology group, has raised its dividend
to 17 cents from 15.5 cents a share following a 20 per cent increase in net
earnings to ADollars 110.1m (USDollars 74m) for the six months ended June.
Directors said the result, achieved on a 19 per cent sales rise to ADollars
2.68bn, reflected higher earnings in 14 of the group's 16 divisions, despite
slow trading in most markets.
The company's biggest profit earner was the food and fermentation division,
which lifted its net contribution from ADollars 62.3m to ADollars 86.6m. The
hardware side improved earnings from ADollars 22.9m to ADollars 23.4m and
investment division profit rose from ADollars 19.1m to ADollars 26.5m.
Mayne Nickless, the diversified transport and security group, has reported a
steep fall in profits for the year ended June. After-tax profit fell 66.6
per cent to ADollars 58.8m on a 2 per cent slide in total operating revenue
to ADollars 2.84m. The dividend is down from 35 cents to 30 cents a share.
The result included a ADollars 47.1m abnormal loss on write-downs at the
European transport operations. In the previous year a ADollars 77.6m
abnormal profit had been taken in, mainly on the sale of shares in Amcor.
