DKr307m from DKr255m, but it made a loss on the insurance account of DKr193m
compared with a profit of DKr36m last year.
The insurance loss reflected a shortfall of DKr275m on credit reinsurance, a
business being discontinued. Premium income was little changed at DKr1.68bn,
while claims rose to DKr1.40bn from DKr1.05bn.
