</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LINTON PARK, the diversified tea coffee and fruit producer and food trader
ultimately controlled by Lawrie Group, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds
4.32m for the six months to June 30.
The outcome, achieved after reduced interest charges of Pounds 684,000
(Pounds 1.05m) was a 'significant improvement' on the comparable Pounds
2.17m, according to Mr Keith FitzGerald, chairman.
