<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 93 / Welding tank for offshore divers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A Pounds 340,000 tank where trainee offshore divers will undergo
examinations in underwater welding inspection is to be built in
Middlesbrough, Cleveland, by the Welding Institute.
The land-based tank, expected to deal with more than 250 examinees a year
after it opens in mid-1994, will replace examinations currently held in open
sea near Plymouth.
</TEXT>
