<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 93 / Security guards see rise in pay
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AVERAGE HOURLY pay for security guards has risen by 12p, to Pounds 3.52 an
hour, in the 12 months to April 1993, a survey by the British Security
Industry Association has found.
Average weekly pay has risen to Pounds 194.63, the highest since October
1991 when guards were working a near-60-hour week against just over 55 hours
this year.
The lowest-paid guards are in the north-east, where average pay for a
55-hour week is just over Pounds 150. Guards in central London earn the
most.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P7382 Security Systems Services.
</IN>
<XX>
